## Step 2: Know the tooling you own

### Core release gates (must pass before anything ships)

```bash
# Gate 1 — always required for code changes
python tools/qa_smoke.py --quick
# Exit 0 = PASS. Runs: determinism_guard + headless sim profiles.

# Gate 2 — required if assets/ was touched
python tools/validate_assets.py --strict --check-attribution
# Exit 0 = PASS. Checks: sprite folders, frame files, audio files, attribution.

# Gate 2b — report-only (non-blocking, useful mid-sprint)
python tools/validate_assets.py --report
```

### Headless sim scenarios (for repro + QA iteration)

```bash
# Standard bounty scenario
python tools/observe_sync.py --seconds 12 --seed 3 --heroes 10 --no-enemies --scenario intent_bounty --qa

# Hero stuck-recovery repro (WK2 contract; forced tile-cage stall)
python tools/observe_sync.py --seconds 20 --seed 3 --heroes 12 --no-enemies --scenario hero_stuck_repro --qa

# Inside-combat gating repro (inside_attack_blocks counter)
python tools/observe_sync.py --seconds 8 --seed 3 --heroes 6 --scenario inside_combat_repro --qa
```

The `--qa` flag emits a `[qa] PASS/FAIL` line and a `[scenario] counters:` line. Exit code 0 = PASS.

### Visual snapshot system

```bash
# Capture scenario snapshots (schema_version 1.1 — machine-independent relpaths)
python tools/capture_screenshots.py --scenario base_overview --seed 3 --out docs/screenshots/<run>/base_overview_seed3 --size 1920x1080 --ticks 0
python tools/capture_screenshots.py --scenario building_catalog --seed 3 --out docs/screenshots/<run>/building_catalog_seed3 --size 1920x1080 --ticks 0
python tools/capture_screenshots.py --scenario enemy_catalog --seed 3 --out docs/screenshots/<run>/enemy_catalog_seed3 --size 1920x1080 --ticks 0
python tools/capture_screenshots.py --scenario ui_panels --seed 3 --out docs/screenshots/<run>/ui_panels_seed3 --size 1920x1080 --ticks 0
python tools/capture_screenshots.py --scenario worker_catalog --seed 3 --out docs/screenshots/<run>/worker_catalog_seed3 --size 1920x1080 --ticks 0

# Build compare gallery
python tools/build_gallery.py --shots docs/screenshots/<run> --refs .cursor/plans/art_examples --out docs/art/compare_gallery.html
```

Manifests must stay machine-independent: no absolute paths, use `relpath` + `run_dir` (schema v1.1).

### Placeholder generator

```bash
# Re-generate all CC0 placeholder PNGs (heroes, enemies, buildings, workers)
python tools/generate_cc0_placeholders.py
```

Regenerating is deterministic and safe to re-run. Run this immediately after updating `tools/assets_manifest.json` — validator will fail until placeholder files exist.

### PM synthesis helper

```bash
# Print per-agent blockers/risks/dependencies from all agent logs
python tools/agent_log_synthesis.py

# Filter to a specific sprint/round
python tools/agent_log_synthesis.py --sprint wk7-ui-polish --round wk7_r1

# Emit JSON for tooling
python tools/agent_log_synthesis.py --json
```

